# File Header Templates
# Use these as starting points for /sentinel:header

## Python (.py)
"""
{filename} — {Role: one sentence describing what this file does}.

Co-modify: {file1.py}, {file2.py}, {file3.py}
Invariants:
  - {Rule that must never break #1}
  - {Rule that must never break #2}
  - {Rule that must never break #3}
Verify: {command to test this file}
"""

## TypeScript (.ts/.tsx)
/**
 * {filename} — {Role: one sentence describing what this file does}.
 *
 * Co-modify: {file1.ts}, {file2.tsx}, {file3.ts}
 * Invariants:
 *   - {Rule that must never break #1}
 *   - {Rule that must never break #2}
 * Verify: {command to test this file}
 */

## Go (.go)
// {filename} — {Role: one sentence describing what this file does}.
//
// Co-modify: {file1.go}, {file2.go}
// Invariants:
//   - {Rule that must never break #1}
//   - {Rule that must never break #2}
// Verify: {command to test this file}

## Rust (.rs)
//! {filename} — {Role: one sentence describing what this file does}.
//!
//! Co-modify: {file1.rs}, {file2.rs}
//! Invariants:
//!   - {Rule that must never break #1}
//!   - {Rule that must never break #2}
//! Verify: {command to test this file}

## Java (.java)
/**
 * {ClassName} — {Role: one sentence describing what this class does}.
 *
 * Co-modify: {File1.java}, {File2.java}
 * Invariants:
 *   - {Rule that must never break #1}
 *   - {Rule that must never break #2}
 * Verify: {command to test this class}
 */
